content:
You push through the glass doors into the temporal greenhouse. Glass panels arch overhead, some frosted with winter's touch while others shimmer with summer heat. Clockwork trees grow in neat rows, their brass leaves ticking softly as they photosynthesize light into time itself. A central fountain bubbles with liquid mercury, its flow reversing every few seconds.

